The paper proposes a new similarity measure for use in supervised learning, specifically the K-nearest neighbor classifier. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed metric is invariant to large differences in some dimensions in the feature space, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks. Finally, the paper mentions experimental results, which could indicate that it belongs to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
